IRS990.Desc: FAMILY HEALTH CENTERS (FHC) PROVIDES MEDICAL SERVICES TO THE COMMUNITY. LOW INCOME, MIGRANT AND SEASONAL FARM WORKERS ARE SERVED ON A SLIDING SCALE BASED ON FEDERAL POVERTY LEVELS. FHC SERVED 11,279 PATIENTS AND HAD 39,130 PATIENT MEDICAL VISITS DURING THE YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: FHC PROVIDES DENTAL SERVICES TO THE COMMUNITY. LOW INCOME, MIGRANT AND SEASONAL FARM WORKERS ARE SERVED ON A SLIDING SCALE BASED ON FEDERAL POVERTY LEVELS. FHC SERVED 6,338 PATIENTS AND HAD 16,561 ENCOUNTERS DURING THE YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: FHC PROVIDES PRESCRIPTIONS TO THE COMMUNITY. LOW INCOME, MIGRANT AND SEASONAL FARM WORKERS ARE SERVED ON A SLIDING SCALE BASED ON FEDERAL POVERTY LEVELS. FHC ISSUED 66,986 PRESCRIPTIONS DURING THE YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: FHC MANAGES THE NUTRITION PROGRAM FOR WOMEN, INFANTS, AND CHILDREN (WIC) FOR THE COUNTY, SERVING 1,420 PARTICIPANTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOTH FHC AND ADVANCE ARE EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAX IS NECESSARY. THE ORGANIZATION EVALUATES UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS WHEREBY THE EFFECT OF THE UNCERTAINTY WOULD BE RECORDED IF THE OUTCOME WAS CONSIDERED PROBABLE AND REASONABLY ESTIMABLE. AS OF MARCH 31, 2023 AND 2022, THE ORGANIZATION HAD NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS REQUIRING ACCRUAL.
FHC MANAGES THE NUTRITION PROGRAM FOR WOMEN, INFANTS, AND CHILDREN (WIC) FOR THE COUNTY, SERVING 1,420 PARTICIPANTS.

A COPY OF THE 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE CFO WHO REVIEWS THE FORM, SCHEDULES AND RELATED ATTACHMENTS. ANY COMMENTS OR QUESTIONS ARE ADDRESSED WITH THE PREPARER AND A FINAL DRAFT IS PRESENTED TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND A COMPLETE COPY PROVIDED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR REVIEW. ONCE MANAGEMENT IS SATISFIED WITH THE 990, THE CEO SIGNS THE FORM 8879-TE AUTHORIZING THE PREPARER TO E-FILE THE RETURN.

EMPLOYEES, DIRECTORS, AND OFFICERS ARE TO AVOID PLACING THEMSELVES IN A POSITION THAT MAY CREATE OR LEAD TO A CONFLICT OF INTEREST OR THE APPEARANCE OF ONE. EMPLOYEES ARE PROHIBITED FROM ENGAGING IN ANY OUTSIDE BUSINESS ACTIVITY, FINANCIAL RELATIONSHIP, OR INVESTMENT THAT CONFLICTS WITH FAMILY HEALTH CENTERS (FHC) INTERESTS, COMPETES WITH FHC, OR MAY INTERFERE WITH THE EMPLOYEE'S RESPONSIBILITIES TO FHC, OR HAS THE APPEARANCE OF INFLUENCING THE EMPLOYEE TO ACT OR MAKE DECISIONS IN A BIASED MANNER OR CONTRARY TO THE BEST INTERESTS OF FHC.

AN EXTERNAL COMPENSATION SURVEY PROCESS (CURRENTLY PERFORMED BY MERCES CONSULTING) COMPARES EACH POSITION TO EXTERNAL MARKET DATA. MERCES HELPED TO IMPLEMENT A GOVERNANCE PROGRAM FOR THE COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S CEO. THE BOARD APPROVES THE COMPENSATION STRUCTURE AND ANY SIGNIFICANT CHANGES.
THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
